    "citation": "Snoeck 2007 17196793",
    "population": "N: 958 Age: - (~16-70) WT: - Seizures: ≥1 - ≥0.167/week",
    "model_type": "PD",
    "objective": "“to identify a dose-response relationship for add-on treatment with levetiracetam based on the data obtained in the four above-mentioned clinical trials, and to identify factors that might influence this dose-response relationship”",
    "covariates": "Included: Differences in baseline, placebo, and dose-dependent treatment effect in probability of seizures occurring.",
    "observations": "Two separate populations modelled: deteriorating and improving patients, which could not be identified using mixture modelling. A clear dose-response relationship could be identified in the improving patients, whereas in the deteriorating patients, such a relationship was not found, as expected. Goodness of fit plot shows good predictability of the seizures, although it is unclear if the population predictions are unbiased, as such a plot is lacking.",
    "dose": "Single and multiple oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "Poisson model of seizure counts",
    "equations": "FPlacebo=theta1 Emax=theta2 ED50=theta3 FDrug=(Emax*DOSE)/(ED50+DOSE) delta=theta4 if(RESP>0 & DOSE>0) lambda=Base*(1-FPlacebo)*(1-FDrug)*exp(eta1) else if(RESP>0 & DOSE==0) lambda=Base*(1-FPlacebo)*exp(eta2) else lambda=Base*(1-delta)*exp(eta3) endif P(x)=exp(-lambda)*((lambda**x)/factorial(x)) Base is number of seizures (presumably per day) at baseline, which was not reported, but for simulations could be provided as a column in the input dataset. FPlacebo is placebo effect, FDrug is drug effect P(x) is the probability of number of seizures x occurring RESP is 0 for non-responder patient and 1 for responder patient DOSE is levetiracetam daily dose in mg Delta is the change in seizure frequency in non-responders, compared to baseline",
    "parameter_values": "theta1=0.11 theta2=0.69 theta3=1408 theta4=-0.45 omega1=0.35 omega2=0.16 omega3=0.081",
    "validation": "Yes (VPC of 100000) / No"
  },
